WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.082 --> 00:00:04.472
<font color="#ffff00">Provided by explosiveskull</font>
https://twitter.com/kaboomskull

2
00:00:04.523 --> 00:00:06.181
<i>Previously on</i>
Dexter: New Blood...

3
00:00:06.222 --> 00:00:07.432
It's me.

4
00:00:07.473 --> 00:00:08.641
Harrison.

5
00:00:08.683 --> 00:00:10.351
[Dexter]
It's just a few things.

6
00:00:10.393 --> 00:00:12.478
in case you decide
you want to stay.

7
00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:14.522
I'm Jim's son.

8
00:00:14.564 --> 00:00:15.523
Son?

9
00:00:15.565 --> 00:00:16.941
I guess you met my mom.

10
00:00:16.983 --> 00:00:18.151
The cop.

11
00:00:18.193 --> 00:00:19.652
Chief of police.

12
00:00:19.694 --> 00:00:21.654
The one dating your dad.

13
00:00:21.696 --> 00:00:23.489
[Fred Jr.]
<i>Matt Caldwell's been cleared.</i>

14
00:00:23.531 --> 00:00:25.366
<i>He wants the gun dropped off
at his dad's lodge.</i>

15
00:00:25.408 --> 00:00:27.911
<i>[mysterious. gentle music]</i>

16
00:00:27.952 --> 00:00:29.204
[gunshot]

17
00:00:29.245 --> 00:00:31.748
[snorting]

18
00:00:31.789 --> 00:00:34.083
[Matt whoops. laughs]

19
00:00:34.125 --> 00:00:36.002
You see what I did there.
uh. Jim?

20
00:00:36.044 --> 00:00:37.337
[grunts]

21
00:00:37.378 --> 00:00:38.504
[inhales deeply]

22
00:00:38.546 --> 00:00:40.048
- [clanging]
- What the...?

23
00:00:40.089 --> 00:00:42.050
You have no idea
what you're doing!

24
00:00:42.091 --> 00:00:43.593
- [grunts]
- [groans]

25
00:00:45.094 --> 00:00:46.721
[Angela] <i>Matt Caldwell
disappeared in the woods</i>

26
00:00:46.763 --> 00:00:48.056
<i>near here last night.</i>

27
00:00:48.097 --> 00:00:49.557
<i>Your place is close</i>

28
00:00:49.599 --> 00:00:50.892
<i>to all the public
hunting grounds.</i>

29
00:00:50.934 --> 00:00:52.060
I was hoping
we could set up base camp

30
00:00:52.101 --> 00:00:53.561
for the search here.

31
00:00:53.603 --> 00:00:55.480
I just found this
about a mile down the trail.

32
00:00:55.521 --> 00:00:57.649
- right before I got to the...
- Highway.

33
00:00:57.690 --> 00:00:59.108
What's going on?

34
00:00:59.150 --> 00:01:00.902
[Angela] Evidence points
to him fleeing the area.

35
00:01:00.944 --> 00:01:02.862
What are you talking about?
My son has disappeared.

36
00:01:02.904 --> 00:01:04.155
and we need to find him now.

37
00:01:04.197 --> 00:01:05.657
We'll keep going
through the night.

38
00:01:05.698 --> 00:01:07.325
Matt's out there.

39
00:01:07.367 --> 00:01:08.409
<i>I'm gonna find him.</i>

40
00:01:08.451 --> 00:01:10.078
<i>if it's the last thing I do.</i>

41
00:01:10.119 --> 00:01:12.789
<i>[low. tense music]</i>

42
00:01:18.419 --> 00:01:20.380
<i>[pulsing. mysterious music]</i>

43
00:01:24.384 --> 00:01:26.177
[Dexter]
<i>Ah. wilderness.</i>

44
00:01:26.219 --> 00:01:28.596
<i>Snow. Ice.</i>

45
00:01:29.514 --> 00:01:31.307
<i>Privacy.</i>

46
00:01:37.313 --> 00:01:40.233
<i>Well. maybe not so much privacy.</i>

47
00:01:41.484 --> 00:01:43.444
<i>I've got a search party
all over my property</i>

48
00:01:43.486 --> 00:01:46.614
<i>looking for someone who's
literally under their feet.</i>

49
00:01:46.656 --> 00:01:48.116
[indistinct chatter]

50
00:01:48.157 --> 00:01:50.827
<i>All because I made
one tiny mistake</i>

51
00:01:50.868 --> 00:01:52.787
<i>and killed someone.</i>

52
00:01:59.794 --> 00:02:01.671
<i>Now I need to search for a way</i>

53
00:02:01.713 --> 00:02:04.048
<i>to get everyone off my land</i>

54
00:02:04.090 --> 00:02:06.843
<i>so I can be a proper dad
for my son.</i>

55
00:02:07.844 --> 00:02:09.220
Okay. Let's go. buddy.

56
00:02:09.262 --> 00:02:10.221
[drone buzzing in distance]

57
00:02:10.263 --> 00:02:11.639
Five more minutes?

58
00:02:11.681 --> 00:02:13.266
This drone is so cool.

59
00:02:13.308 --> 00:02:14.559
We're meeting with
the school principal. First day.

60
00:02:14.600 --> 00:02:15.601
Don't want to be late.

61
00:02:15.643 --> 00:02:16.978
Okay.

62
00:02:19.188 --> 00:02:20.773
- Thanks. Logan.
- Oh. yeah. Anytime.

63
00:02:20.815 --> 00:02:22.066
Oh. hey!

64
00:02:22.108 --> 00:02:23.568
You want to wrestle?

65
00:02:24.694 --> 00:02:26.279
I'm the assistant coach
of the high school team.

66
00:02:26.321 --> 00:02:27.280
You should try out.

67
00:02:27.322 --> 00:02:28.656
[Harrison]
Cool.

68
00:02:28.698 --> 00:02:29.991
Y-Yeah.
I'll-I'll think about it.

69
00:02:30.033 --> 00:02:32.243
Jim. you okay
with your son wrestling?

70
00:02:32.285 --> 00:02:33.661
Uh... sure.

71
00:02:33.703 --> 00:02:34.829
Sounds good.

72
00:02:34.871 --> 00:02:35.872
Yeah. it's a great sport.

73
00:02:35.913 --> 00:02:37.790
Teaches you personal growth.

74
00:02:37.832 --> 00:02:39.125
confidence. mental toughness.

75
00:02:39.167 --> 00:02:40.209
Logan!

76
00:02:40.251 --> 00:02:41.711
We're going back to the station.

77
00:02:41.753 --> 00:02:43.171
There's been a break
in the case.

78
00:02:43.212 --> 00:02:45.631
[Dexter]
<i>A break in the case? Perfect.</i>

79
00:02:45.673 --> 00:02:46.674
What happened?

80
00:02:46.716 --> 00:02:48.343
Talk later. Jim.

81
00:02:50.345 --> 00:02:52.180
What do you think it is?
You think they found the body?

82
00:02:52.221 --> 00:02:54.474
We'll find out soon enough.

83
00:02:54.515 --> 00:02:55.767
Let's go.

84
00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:03.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

85
00:03:04.859 --> 00:03:06.944
[Strode]
<i>By the way. Jim.</i>

86
00:03:06.986 --> 00:03:09.947
<i>my husband loves that
fishing rod you talked him into.</i>

87
00:03:09.989 --> 00:03:11.324
Great.

88
00:03:11.366 --> 00:03:12.533
He said you were right.

89
00:03:12.575 --> 00:03:14.369
Having that fast action
helps him

90
00:03:14.410 --> 00:03:15.870
put more pressure on the fish.

91
00:03:15.912 --> 00:03:17.538
Glad it worked out.

92
00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:19.040
[Strode]
Me. too.

93
00:03:19.082 --> 00:03:21.542
So. I've been looking
at Harrison's grades.

94
00:03:21.584 --> 00:03:23.169
and I have some concerns.

95
00:03:23.211 --> 00:03:25.380
- Concerns? [exhales]
- In just one year.

96
00:03:25.421 --> 00:03:27.673
he went from a 3.8
down to a 1.2.

97
00:03:27.715 --> 00:03:29.884
then back to a 3.0.

98
00:03:29.926 --> 00:03:31.302
Why is that?

99
00:03:31.344 --> 00:03:33.638
I'm not exactly sure.

100
00:03:33.679 --> 00:03:36.849
Uh. my stepmom died.

101
00:03:36.891 --> 00:03:38.684
Oh. Um...

102
00:03:38.726 --> 00:03:40.895
I'm so sorry.

103
00:03:40.937 --> 00:03:43.356
Is that why you moved
from Argentina to Miami?

104
00:03:43.398 --> 00:03:44.690
Yep.

105
00:03:44.732 --> 00:03:47.568
So. who did you move
to Miami with?

106
00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:51.239
Uh. I was placed
in the foster care system.

107
00:03:52.240 --> 00:03:53.574
Foster care?

108
00:03:54.492 --> 00:03:55.576
And where were you?

109
00:03:55.618 --> 00:03:57.286
[Deb]
<i>Yeah.</i>

110
00:03:57.328 --> 00:03:59.330
Why don't you tell them
why you left your beloved son?

111
00:04:02.333 --> 00:04:04.961
[stammers]
Things were complicated. ma'am.

112
00:04:05.002 --> 00:04:06.087
Um...

113
00:04:06.129 --> 00:04:08.256
My stepmom and I had just moved.

114
00:04:08.297 --> 00:04:11.926
And when she died. uh.
Jim had no way of reaching me.

115
00:04:11.968 --> 00:04:13.886
- It's not his fault.
- [footsteps approaching]

116
00:04:13.928 --> 00:04:14.887
Hi. Jim.

117
00:04:14.929 --> 00:04:15.930
Oh. hey. Tess.

118
00:04:15.972 --> 00:04:17.765
You must be Harrison.

119
00:04:17.807 --> 00:04:20.101
I'm Ms. Silvera.
the science teacher here.

120
00:04:20.143 --> 00:04:21.853
I heard you speaking Spanish
the other day.

121
00:04:21.894 --> 00:04:23.354
Uh. <i>¿de dónde eres?</i>

122
00:04:23.396 --> 00:04:25.022
Puerto Rico.

123
00:04:25.064 --> 00:04:27.024
<i>¿Dónde aprendiste español?</i>

124
00:04:27.066 --> 00:04:29.610
I lived in Argentina
for a few years.

125
00:04:30.611 --> 00:04:32.196
- [chuckles]
- Ms. Silvera

126
00:04:32.238 --> 00:04:34.073
will be administering
Harrison's placement exam.

127
00:04:34.115 --> 00:04:35.783
Then we'll know
which grade level he's at.

128
00:04:35.825 --> 00:04:39.036
And you'll know a little more
about your son.

129
00:04:40.663 --> 00:04:42.248
[chuckles]
I'm not surprised

130
00:04:42.290 --> 00:04:43.958
the salon was shut down
for health violations.

131
00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:45.626
I mean. Sally has
really been letting things slide

132
00:04:45.668 --> 00:04:48.796
ever since Edgar fell off
the wagon and started...

133
00:04:48.838 --> 00:04:50.798
Rose-Ellen.
I will call you later.

134
00:04:51.799 --> 00:04:53.426
- Hey. Is Angela around?
- [chuckles]

135
00:04:53.468 --> 00:04:54.844
Conference room.

136
00:04:54.886 --> 00:04:56.971
Apparently.
Reservation Land Management

137
00:04:57.013 --> 00:04:59.849
has footage of Matt Caldwell
shooting that deer.

138
00:04:59.891 --> 00:05:02.143
- Footage?
- Who knew there were cameras

139
00:05:02.185 --> 00:05:03.728
out there?
[laughs]

140
00:05:03.769 --> 00:05:04.812
[Dexter]
<i>I sure didn't.</i>

141
00:05:04.854 --> 00:05:05.855
Huh.

142
00:05:05.897 --> 00:05:07.565
What do they even need them for?

143
00:05:07.607 --> 00:05:09.734
I mean. we know how deer mate.

144
00:05:09.775 --> 00:05:12.069
- [chuckles]
- Jim. I need to talk to you.

145
00:05:12.111 --> 00:05:14.071
<i>[slow. tense music]</i>

146
00:05:24.290 --> 00:05:26.167
[Dexter]
<i>Great.</i>

147
00:05:26.209 --> 00:05:28.836
<i>I'm gonna be brought down
by three small-town cops...</i>

148
00:05:28.878 --> 00:05:31.130
This is Sam. from Land
and Wildlife Management.

149
00:05:31.172 --> 00:05:32.757
<i>...and a zoologist.</i>

150
00:05:34.884 --> 00:05:37.178
We need you
to clear something up for us.

151
00:05:38.137 --> 00:05:39.680
Happy to.

152
00:05:43.518 --> 00:05:45.353
Heat signatures?

153
00:05:45.394 --> 00:05:46.479
It's pretty cool. huh?

154
00:05:46.521 --> 00:05:48.272
Very.
[exhales]

155
00:05:48.314 --> 00:05:50.775
[Angela]
Okay. pause it.

156
00:05:50.816 --> 00:05:54.195
Does that look like the rifle
you sold to Matt?

157
00:05:55.863 --> 00:05:58.032
Uh...

158
00:05:58.074 --> 00:06:01.077
I'm guessing it's a...

159
00:06:01.118 --> 00:06:04.080
Modern Outfitters MC6 with...

160
00:06:04.121 --> 00:06:07.124
what looks like a very
distinctive Leupold scope.

161
00:06:07.166 --> 00:06:09.043
It's just like the one
I sold Matt.

162
00:06:09.085 --> 00:06:10.836
So you're saying
that this is my son.

163
00:06:10.878 --> 00:06:13.422
Well. this confirms
that Matt shot the deer.

164
00:06:13.464 --> 00:06:15.758
And gets us no closer
to finding him.

165
00:06:15.800 --> 00:06:19.011
Actually. we did find
one more thing.

166
00:06:19.053 --> 00:06:20.930
From the next quadrant over.

167
00:06:20.972 --> 00:06:24.433
about 20 seconds earlier.

168
00:06:28.563 --> 00:06:30.565
He's heading for the same spot
as the first guy.

169
00:06:30.606 --> 00:06:32.733
[Kurt] There's someone else
in the woods.

170
00:06:32.775 --> 00:06:35.403
We need the angle
that shows where they went.

171
00:06:35.444 --> 00:06:37.572
- There's a blind spot.
- [Kurt] Blind spot? Why is there

172
00:06:37.613 --> 00:06:39.073
a fucking blind spot?

173
00:06:39.115 --> 00:06:41.409
This system is set up
for animal tracking.

174
00:06:41.450 --> 00:06:42.910
not crime surveillance.

175
00:06:42.952 --> 00:06:44.328
There's gonna be tons
of blind spots.

176
00:06:44.370 --> 00:06:46.247
Ah. Goddamn it.

177
00:06:46.289 --> 00:06:47.873
Contact tribal police.

178
00:06:47.915 --> 00:06:49.917
Call Albany
and get CSI out here and. um.

179
00:06:49.959 --> 00:06:51.711
go secure the crime scene ASAP.

180
00:06:51.752 --> 00:06:52.920
Yep. yep.

181
00:06:52.962 --> 00:06:54.839
Oh. so now it's a crime scene?

182
00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:56.591
[Angela]
Yes.

183
00:06:56.632 --> 00:06:58.259
[Kurt]
You had no idea

184
00:06:58.301 --> 00:07:00.428
there were cameras
all over your people's lands.

185
00:07:00.469 --> 00:07:01.596
You've been treating this
like it's some kind

186
00:07:01.637 --> 00:07:03.431
of goddamn missing persons case.

187
00:07:03.472 --> 00:07:06.058
and. the whole time. you had a
suspect under your fucking nose?

188
00:07:06.100 --> 00:07:07.810
That's the way
these things work. Kurt.

189
00:07:07.852 --> 00:07:09.562
We find new evidence.
Things change.

190
00:07:09.604 --> 00:07:11.355
Now it's
a criminal investigation.

191
00:07:11.397 --> 00:07:13.190
Look. if this guy did
something to Matt.

192
00:07:13.232 --> 00:07:14.942
we'll find him.

193
00:07:17.612 --> 00:07:19.405
You could check
hunting licenses.

194
00:07:19.447 --> 00:07:21.324
We sell 'em at the store.
I can make a list.

195
00:07:21.365 --> 00:07:23.034
<i>Which I won't be on.</i>

196
00:07:23.075 --> 00:07:25.244
Let's interview everyone
who came in contact with Matt

197
00:07:25.286 --> 00:07:27.079
in the 48 hours
before he disappeared.

198
00:07:27.121 --> 00:07:28.289
[Logan]
On it.

199
00:07:28.331 --> 00:07:30.291
Maybe he wasn't out there alone.

200
00:07:34.670 --> 00:07:36.756
[indistinct chatter]

201
00:07:40.092 --> 00:07:41.719
[Zach laughing]

202
00:07:41.761 --> 00:07:43.638
What's up. Zach?

203
00:07:43.679 --> 00:07:46.265
Yo. Yo. they got you taking
classes already. or what?

204
00:07:46.307 --> 00:07:48.267
Not yet. I-I just took
the placement test.

205
00:07:48.309 --> 00:07:50.102
It was cake.

206
00:07:50.144 --> 00:07:52.271
Check out the big brain on H.

207
00:07:52.313 --> 00:07:53.898
[chuckles]

208
00:07:53.939 --> 00:07:56.484
Yo. man. Look at this shit.

209
00:07:56.525 --> 00:07:58.986
- [laughter]
- [clamoring]

210
00:07:59.028 --> 00:08:00.321
Who's Ethan?

211
00:08:00.363 --> 00:08:01.781
That ballsack over there.

212
00:08:01.822 --> 00:08:03.741
[laughter]

213
00:08:03.783 --> 00:08:05.826
[phone chimes]

214
00:08:08.871 --> 00:08:11.248
Hey. you should see
the shit he sends her.

215
00:08:12.833 --> 00:08:14.585
Ooh-ooh. oh-oh.

216
00:08:14.627 --> 00:08:17.088
Somebody's in love!

217
00:08:17.129 --> 00:08:19.507
That's fucked up.

218
00:08:19.548 --> 00:08:22.009
[Zach]
Right? [laughing]

219
00:08:35.856 --> 00:08:38.484
Hunting licenses...
all from this year.

220
00:08:38.526 --> 00:08:40.820
Hopefully this'll help
point you guys

221
00:08:40.861 --> 00:08:43.447
- in the right direction.
- Great. Thanks.

222
00:08:43.489 --> 00:08:45.491
Wildlife cameras.

223
00:08:45.533 --> 00:08:47.201
Who knew?

224
00:08:47.243 --> 00:08:48.828
Not me.

225
00:08:48.869 --> 00:08:49.995
Guys like Kurt
have been doubting me

226
00:08:50.037 --> 00:08:51.539
ever since I joined the force.

227
00:08:51.580 --> 00:08:53.457
Now I've given him
all the ammunition he needs.

228
00:08:53.499 --> 00:08:56.711
I was calling off the search
after the first day

229
00:08:56.752 --> 00:08:59.630
because I found a glove.

230
00:08:59.672 --> 00:09:01.966
What was I thinking?

231
00:09:02.007 --> 00:09:03.759
[Dexter]
<i>What I wanted you to think.</i>

232
00:09:03.801 --> 00:09:06.804
If I learned anything. it's that
people don't just disappear.

233
00:09:08.389 --> 00:09:10.057
There's always a reason.

234
00:09:10.099 --> 00:09:11.851
Well. you're a good cop.

235
00:09:11.892 --> 00:09:14.019
You'll find him.

236
00:09:18.524 --> 00:09:21.026
Uh. that was fast.

237
00:09:21.068 --> 00:09:23.571
Maybe we'll start getting
some answers.

238
00:09:23.612 --> 00:09:26.198
Damien.

239
00:09:32.246 --> 00:09:34.123
Ah. Damn it!

240
00:09:38.085 --> 00:09:39.920
You need another hand?

241
00:09:39.962 --> 00:09:42.047
Oh!
[chuckles]

242
00:09:42.089 --> 00:09:43.924
Much obliged.
[grunts]

243
00:09:43.966 --> 00:09:46.719
Are you the CSI from Albany?

244
00:09:46.761 --> 00:09:49.472
Well. originally
I'm from St. Louis. but...

245
00:09:49.513 --> 00:09:51.932
You mind if I watch you
work the scene?

246
00:09:51.974 --> 00:09:54.769
I'm a big fan
of those CSI shows.

247
00:09:54.810 --> 00:09:56.604
[Kurt]
Hey. I'm coming. too.

248
00:09:56.645 --> 00:09:58.856
It's my son they're looking for.

249
00:09:59.482 --> 00:10:02.735
As long as you both
stay outside the crime scene

250
00:10:02.777 --> 00:10:04.904
and don't disturb
the corpus delicti.

251
00:10:04.945 --> 00:10:06.238
Corpus de-what?

252
00:10:06.280 --> 00:10:08.115
It's Latin
for "body of evidence."

253
00:10:08.157 --> 00:10:09.784
Damn it.

254
00:10:17.333 --> 00:10:19.710
[Dexter]
<i>Not out of the woods yet.</i>

255
00:10:21.003 --> 00:10:22.963
What you doing. Mr. Church?

256
00:10:23.005 --> 00:10:26.300
Some of the blood coagulated
differently than the rest.

257
00:10:26.342 --> 00:10:29.470
so I'm testing it

258
00:10:29.512 --> 00:10:32.097
to see if it came from the deer

259
00:10:32.139 --> 00:10:34.642
or if it's human.

260
00:10:34.683 --> 00:10:36.769
[Dexter]
<i>Exactly what I would've done.</i>

261
00:10:36.811 --> 00:10:38.979
Blood is the body's...

262
00:10:39.021 --> 00:10:39.980
[Dexter]
<i>Truth.</i>

263
00:10:40.022 --> 00:10:42.233
...truth.

264
00:10:48.155 --> 00:10:50.157
It's human.

265
00:10:50.199 --> 00:10:52.326
Someone may have mixed it in
with the deer's blood

266
00:10:52.368 --> 00:10:54.703
so we'd overlook it.

267
00:10:54.745 --> 00:10:57.331
[Dexter]
<i>Uh-oh. This guy's good.</i>

268
00:10:59.875 --> 00:11:02.336
Kurt. we don't even know
if that's Matt's blood.

269
00:11:02.378 --> 00:11:04.338
And even if it is.
he could've cut himself.

270
00:11:04.380 --> 00:11:07.174
People cut themselves
dressing animals all the time.

271
00:11:07.216 --> 00:11:09.510
Or maybe it's from
the other guy who was out here.

272
00:11:09.552 --> 00:11:11.762
So. what. somebody attacked Matt

273
00:11:11.804 --> 00:11:13.848
because of that stupid deer

274
00:11:13.889 --> 00:11:15.599
and he fought him off?

275
00:11:15.641 --> 00:11:17.309
- Is that it?
- It's possible.

276
00:11:17.351 --> 00:11:19.103
Shit.

277
00:11:19.144 --> 00:11:21.021
Damien.
what do you think happened?

278
00:11:25.526 --> 00:11:27.945
[Dexter]
<i>Come on. Damien. fail me now.</i>

279
00:11:30.823 --> 00:11:33.367
The victim came from over there.

280
00:11:33.409 --> 00:11:36.871
- [whoops]
- The attacker from over there.

281
00:11:36.912 --> 00:11:39.164
Judging by the pool

282
00:11:39.206 --> 00:11:41.417
of blood.
they met up right around here.

283
00:11:41.458 --> 00:11:44.086
where the deer was shot.

284
00:11:44.128 --> 00:11:45.921
There was some sort of...

285
00:11:45.963 --> 00:11:48.048
altercation.

286
00:11:48.090 --> 00:11:49.925
The attacker

287
00:11:49.967 --> 00:11:52.219
overpowered the victim.

288
00:11:52.261 --> 00:11:54.680
Knocked him down.

289
00:11:54.722 --> 00:11:57.349
The victim then fell...

290
00:11:57.391 --> 00:11:59.685
backwards...

291
00:11:59.727 --> 00:12:02.771
hitting his head right about...

292
00:12:08.903 --> 00:12:10.738
Huh.

293
00:12:10.779 --> 00:12:13.073
There was a rock here.

294
00:12:13.115 --> 00:12:15.701
Must've been removed
after the attack.

295
00:12:15.743 --> 00:12:18.245
I suspect it caused
a head injury.

296
00:12:18.287 --> 00:12:21.165
Wait. so what exactly
are you saying happened here?

297
00:12:21.206 --> 00:12:23.667
[chuckles]
What I'm saying is somebody

298
00:12:23.709 --> 00:12:26.253
committed an attack.
then tried to cover it up.

299
00:12:27.588 --> 00:12:29.256
We're looking at foul play.

300
00:12:29.298 --> 00:12:32.426
[Dexter] <i>I've gotten rusty
in my abstinence.</i>

301
00:12:32.468 --> 00:12:34.094
Well. what now?

302
00:12:34.136 --> 00:12:36.680
How do we find the son of
a bitch that did this to my son?

303
00:12:36.722 --> 00:12:38.223
We still don't know
whose blood this is.

304
00:12:38.265 --> 00:12:39.892
We need to establish that first.

305
00:12:39.934 --> 00:12:41.518
That's true.

306
00:12:42.645 --> 00:12:44.271
[Angela] Kurt. with your
permission. I want Damian

307
00:12:44.313 --> 00:12:46.065
to do a familial DNA test.

308
00:12:46.106 --> 00:12:48.233
We'd run a sample of your DNA
against the human blood

309
00:12:48.275 --> 00:12:49.777
that we just found and...

310
00:12:49.818 --> 00:12:52.321
if it's a match.
it will confirm that it's Matt.

311
00:12:55.783 --> 00:12:58.619
[stammers] All right.
W-Whatever. Whatever you need.

312
00:13:01.747 --> 00:13:03.415
[phone buzzing]

313
00:13:03.457 --> 00:13:05.501
[overlapping indistinct chatter]

314
00:13:06.835 --> 00:13:07.836
This is Jim.

315
00:13:07.878 --> 00:13:09.004
[Strode]
<i>Hello. Jim.</i>

316
00:13:09.046 --> 00:13:10.798
<i>It's Principal Strode.</i>

317
00:13:10.839 --> 00:13:12.967
Yeah. I'm kind of in the middle
of something right now.

318
00:13:13.008 --> 00:13:14.885
<i>It's about Harrison.</i>

319
00:13:14.927 --> 00:13:17.429
<i>We need you
to come down to the school.</i>

320
00:13:17.471 --> 00:13:19.306
Harrison scored higher
than any student has

321
00:13:19.348 --> 00:13:21.392
ever scored
on the school placement exam.

322
00:13:21.433 --> 00:13:23.477
So you had me come
all the way down here

323
00:13:23.519 --> 00:13:25.229
to tell me how great my kid is?

324
00:13:26.772 --> 00:13:28.732
Tess left the room
for 15 minutes.

325
00:13:28.774 --> 00:13:31.068
And when she came back.
he was done.

326
00:13:31.110 --> 00:13:33.570
- The test was easy.
- The test was easy.

327
00:13:33.612 --> 00:13:35.114
Some of the questions
on this test are

328
00:13:35.155 --> 00:13:36.657
for Advanced Placement students.

329
00:13:36.699 --> 00:13:38.492
College-level.
I believe while Tess was gone.

330
00:13:38.534 --> 00:13:39.994
Harrison used his cell phone
to look up answers.

331
00:13:40.035 --> 00:13:41.495
I did not.

332
00:13:41.537 --> 00:13:43.747
Did you cheat?

333
00:13:43.789 --> 00:13:45.624
You accusing me of lying...

334
00:13:45.666 --> 00:13:46.875
Jim?

335
00:13:46.917 --> 00:13:48.293
No.

336
00:13:48.335 --> 00:13:49.837
I'm happy to proctor
the exam again.

337
00:13:49.878 --> 00:13:52.006
There you go.
You take it again. no phones.

338
00:13:52.047 --> 00:13:53.173
I did not cheat.

339
00:13:53.215 --> 00:13:54.842
Then you'll prove it.

340
00:13:54.883 --> 00:13:56.510
Oh. thanks for having my back.

341
00:13:56.552 --> 00:13:58.220
Like always.

342
00:13:59.847 --> 00:14:01.849
[sighs]

343
00:14:01.890 --> 00:14:03.976
- [indistinct chatter]
- [fire crackling]

344
00:14:10.190 --> 00:14:11.525
[Dexter]
Tea.

345
00:14:11.567 --> 00:14:13.444
Oh. that's perfect.

346
00:14:13.485 --> 00:14:15.529
I'm about to head out.

347
00:14:16.613 --> 00:14:19.283
Got to check on the results
of the DNA test

348
00:14:19.324 --> 00:14:21.160
and confirm the search dog team.

349
00:14:21.201 --> 00:14:22.870
Search dogs?

350
00:14:22.911 --> 00:14:25.164
- Yep. Should be here tomorrow.
- Wow.

351
00:14:25.205 --> 00:14:27.041
You're ramping things up.

352
00:14:28.250 --> 00:14:31.378
At this point. I'm just hoping
it's not too late.

353
00:14:31.420 --> 00:14:33.047
It's not.

354
00:14:43.432 --> 00:14:45.726
Search dogs? Jesus fuck. Dex.

355
00:14:45.768 --> 00:14:47.561
- I know.
- You have to move Matt's body.

356
00:14:47.603 --> 00:14:49.730
Those dogs are gonna walk
a straight line from the crime

357
00:14:49.772 --> 00:14:51.899
- scene to your fucking firepit.
- I know.

358
00:14:51.940 --> 00:14:53.442
It's not just about you anymore.

359
00:14:53.484 --> 00:14:55.861
- I know!
- Do you?

360
00:14:55.903 --> 00:14:57.404
It was a one-time slipup.

361
00:14:57.446 --> 00:14:58.781
It doesn't change who I am.

362
00:14:58.822 --> 00:15:00.616
Who is that. exactly?

363
00:15:00.657 --> 00:15:02.701
- Stop.
- Or what?

364
00:15:04.203 --> 00:15:05.954
You gonna kill me again?

365
00:15:05.996 --> 00:15:07.664
Or are other people gonna die?

366
00:15:07.706 --> 00:15:09.416
Because that's
what always happens. right?

367
00:15:09.458 --> 00:15:11.794
- Right?!
- Not this time. No.

368
00:15:11.835 --> 00:15:13.212
[knocking]

369
00:15:13.253 --> 00:15:14.171
[Harrison]
What are you doing in there?

370
00:15:14.213 --> 00:15:16.048
All yours.

371
00:15:18.383 --> 00:15:20.761
All yours.

372
00:15:20.803 --> 00:15:22.679
Just so you know.

373
00:15:22.721 --> 00:15:24.098
Retook the test.

374
00:15:24.139 --> 00:15:25.974
Got a higher score
than the first time.

375
00:15:26.016 --> 00:15:27.351
That's great.

376
00:15:27.392 --> 00:15:28.936
Congrats.

377
00:15:33.649 --> 00:15:35.400
[sighs]

378
00:15:35.442 --> 00:15:37.486
[phone buzzing]

379
00:15:42.491 --> 00:15:44.576
This is Kurt.

380
00:15:44.618 --> 00:15:46.620
It's Chief Bishop.

381
00:15:46.662 --> 00:15:48.914
Apologies for calling so late.

382
00:15:48.956 --> 00:15:51.250
Good news or bad?

383
00:15:51.291 --> 00:15:54.294
<i>I'm afraid it's a match.</i>

384
00:15:54.336 --> 00:15:57.798
<i>The blood we found is
almost certainly Matt's.</i>

385
00:15:58.757 --> 00:16:00.634
I'm sorry.

386
00:16:02.970 --> 00:16:05.180
Well. you should be.

387
00:16:05.222 --> 00:16:07.516
You made my son out
to be some kind of criminal.

388
00:16:07.558 --> 00:16:09.685
I wasn't wrong about that.

389
00:16:09.726 --> 00:16:10.978
Excuse me?

390
00:16:11.019 --> 00:16:12.312
<i>Matt shot a white buck</i>

391
00:16:12.354 --> 00:16:13.981
<i>on sovereign Seneca territory.</i>

392
00:16:14.022 --> 00:16:15.315
A crime that carries a sentence

393
00:16:15.357 --> 00:16:16.567
of at least
several thousand dollars.

394
00:16:16.608 --> 00:16:18.402
I don't give a shit about that!

395
00:16:18.443 --> 00:16:20.529
I only care what happened
to my son.

396
00:16:20.571 --> 00:16:23.031
My guess is
that the other person

397
00:16:23.073 --> 00:16:25.993
out there in the woods
saw Matt shoot the deer.

398
00:16:26.034 --> 00:16:27.995
<i>and wasn't too happy about it.</i>

399
00:16:28.036 --> 00:16:29.496
Well. at least now
you're starting

400
00:16:29.538 --> 00:16:31.248
to sound like a real cop.

401
00:16:31.290 --> 00:16:33.167
With all due respect.

402
00:16:33.208 --> 00:16:35.627
I have been running this search
with zero state funding.

403
00:16:35.669 --> 00:16:37.421
At the crack of dawn.
I'll have 60 volunteers

404
00:16:37.462 --> 00:16:39.006
as far out as Clarke Mountains.

405
00:16:39.047 --> 00:16:40.799
The next day. we will cover
the entire quarry.

406
00:16:40.841 --> 00:16:42.009
The day after that.
we will canvass the caves.

407
00:16:42.050 --> 00:16:43.260
We will not stop

408
00:16:43.302 --> 00:16:45.095
<i>until we find your son.</i>

409
00:16:45.137 --> 00:16:47.598
The caves?
You think he's that far out?

410
00:16:48.807 --> 00:16:51.018
Matt's a smart guy.

411
00:16:51.059 --> 00:16:52.853
Maybe he went
looking for shelter.

412
00:16:52.895 --> 00:16:54.855
What about the summer camp?

413
00:16:54.897 --> 00:16:57.357
<i>I'm having a group splinter off.
We're searching there. too.</i>

414
00:16:58.358 --> 00:16:59.484
[sighs]

415
00:16:59.526 --> 00:17:01.236
Listen. Kurt.

416
00:17:01.278 --> 00:17:03.071
I know you're grieving.

417
00:17:03.113 --> 00:17:04.406
- <i>And I...</i>
- Just call me

418
00:17:04.448 --> 00:17:06.200
when you have an actual lead.

419
00:17:12.122 --> 00:17:15.083
[sighs]
Goddamn it.

420
00:17:15.125 --> 00:17:17.127
<i>["Avalanche" by Leonard Cohen]</i>

421
00:17:34.978 --> 00:17:37.898
<i>Well. I stepped into</i>

422
00:17:37.940 --> 00:17:40.734
<i>An avalanche</i>

423
00:17:40.776 --> 00:17:44.655
<i>It covered up my soul</i>

424
00:17:46.281 --> 00:17:49.493
<i>When I am not this hunchback</i>

425
00:17:49.534 --> 00:17:51.328
<i>That you see</i>

426
00:17:51.370 --> 00:17:54.998
<i>I sleep
beneath the golden hill</i>

427
00:17:56.708 --> 00:18:01.213
<i>You who wish to conquer pain</i>

428
00:18:01.255 --> 00:18:03.757
<i>You must learn. learn</i>

429
00:18:03.799 --> 00:18:06.885
<i>To serve me well</i>

430
00:18:17.562 --> 00:18:20.816
<i>He does not ask for your</i>

431
00:18:20.857 --> 00:18:24.444
<i>Company. not at the center</i>

432
00:18:24.486 --> 00:18:28.573
<i>The center of the world</i>

433
00:18:30.325 --> 00:18:33.036
[panting]

434
00:18:45.674 --> 00:18:47.759
[pants]

435
00:18:49.511 --> 00:18:52.472
[Dexter]
<i>First the glove. now the scent.</i>

436
00:18:52.514 --> 00:18:55.058
<i>One plus one equals...</i>

437
00:18:55.100 --> 00:18:57.144
<i>Matt.</i>

438
00:19:18.790 --> 00:19:20.792
<i>[Del Shannon's "Runaway"
playing]</i>

439
00:19:25.505 --> 00:19:29.718
<i>♪ As I walk along. I wonder ♪</i>

440
00:19:29.760 --> 00:19:33.096
<i>♪ A-what went wrong
with our love ♪</i>

441
00:19:33.138 --> 00:19:36.516
<i>♪ A love that was so strong ♪</i>

442
00:19:38.310 --> 00:19:40.187
<i>♪ And as I still walk on... ♪</i>

443
00:19:40.228 --> 00:19:41.980
[buzzer sounds]

444
00:19:42.022 --> 00:19:44.733
<i>♪ ...of the things
we've done together ♪</i>

445
00:19:44.775 --> 00:19:47.736
<i>♪ While our hearts were young ♪</i>

446
00:19:50.197 --> 00:19:52.407
<i>♪ I'm a-walkin' in the rain ♪</i>

447
00:19:52.449 --> 00:19:56.036
<i>♪ Tears are fallin'
and I feel a pain ♪</i>

448
00:19:56.078 --> 00:19:59.373
<i>♪ A-wishin' you were here
by me ♪</i>

449
00:19:59.414 --> 00:20:02.042
<i>♪ To end this misery ♪</i>

450
00:20:02.084 --> 00:20:06.755
<i>♪ I wonder.
I wa-wa-wa-wa-wonder ♪</i>

451
00:20:08.382 --> 00:20:11.968
<i>♪ Why. why-why-why-why-why ♪</i>

452
00:20:12.010 --> 00:20:14.137
<i>♪ She ran away ♪</i>

453
00:20:14.179 --> 00:20:16.556
<i>♪ And I wonder ♪</i>

454
00:20:16.598 --> 00:20:18.892
<i>♪ Where she will stay ♪</i>

455
00:20:18.934 --> 00:20:21.978
<i>♪ My little runaway ♪</i>

456
00:20:22.020 --> 00:20:25.190
<i>♪ My run-run-run-run-runaway ♪</i>

457
00:20:41.998 --> 00:20:43.917
[exhales slowly]

458
00:20:43.959 --> 00:20:46.670
[gunshot echoes]

459
00:20:48.588 --> 00:20:51.258
[Dexter] <i>Wouldn't want
to be prey around here.</i>

460
00:20:51.299 --> 00:20:54.428
<i>Hunters get up way too early.</i>

461
00:20:54.469 --> 00:20:57.264
<i>♪ And I wonder ♪</i>

462
00:20:57.305 --> 00:21:00.100
<i>♪ Where she will stay ♪</i>

463
00:21:00.142 --> 00:21:02.185
<i>♪ My little runaway... ♪</i>

464
00:21:02.227 --> 00:21:04.354
[inhales deeply]

465
00:21:04.396 --> 00:21:06.648
[exhales]

466
00:21:07.899 --> 00:21:09.609
[exhales]

467
00:21:11.903 --> 00:21:13.447
Looks like you had a long night.

468
00:21:13.488 --> 00:21:16.116
Yeah. one of Mrs. Gross' sheep
was lambing.

469
00:21:16.158 --> 00:21:18.577
She needed my help.

470
00:21:18.618 --> 00:21:21.913
I'm sorry I wasn't here to...
make you breakfast.

471
00:21:21.955 --> 00:21:23.623
Don't worry about it.
[sniffles]

472
00:21:23.665 --> 00:21:25.459
I've learned
to take care of myself.

473
00:21:26.835 --> 00:21:28.295
I got to get to school.

474
00:21:29.463 --> 00:21:31.465
You gonna drive me.
or should I walk?

475
00:21:31.506 --> 00:21:33.425
[Dexter]
<i>Why not?</i>

476
00:21:33.467 --> 00:21:35.635
<i>Not like it's been
a long night or anything.</i>

477
00:21:40.891 --> 00:21:43.018
[clears throat]

478
00:21:43.059 --> 00:21:45.437
[Logan]
Morning. Jimbo!

479
00:21:45.479 --> 00:21:47.606
Got a sec?

480
00:21:47.647 --> 00:21:49.649
Sure.

481
00:21:49.691 --> 00:21:52.861
So. uh. we got the results
from the DNA test.

482
00:21:52.903 --> 00:21:54.696
It's confirmed.

483
00:21:54.738 --> 00:21:55.864
The blood was Matt's.

484
00:21:55.906 --> 00:21:57.616
[sighs] Oh.

485
00:21:57.657 --> 00:21:58.992
I'm sorry to hear that.

486
00:21:59.034 --> 00:22:00.785
<i>But not surprised.</i>

487
00:22:00.827 --> 00:22:02.204
Anyway. um...

488
00:22:02.245 --> 00:22:04.122
Angela has tasked me
to interview everyone

489
00:22:04.164 --> 00:22:05.874
who saw Matt in the days
before he went missing.

490
00:22:05.916 --> 00:22:07.459
so I just need to ask you
a few questions.

491
00:22:07.501 --> 00:22:08.793
- It won't take long.
- I have to take Harrison

492
00:22:08.835 --> 00:22:10.670
to school. but. uh...

493
00:22:10.712 --> 00:22:12.672
I could stop by the station
during lunch?

494
00:22:12.714 --> 00:22:14.341
Cool.

495
00:22:14.382 --> 00:22:16.176
Appreciate that.

496
00:22:17.385 --> 00:22:19.763
Oh. and. uh. Harrison?

497
00:22:20.722 --> 00:22:22.641
Saw you signed up for wrestling.

498
00:22:22.682 --> 00:22:24.184
Yeah. Yeah. Can't wait.

499
00:22:24.226 --> 00:22:25.936
Real men are made on the mat.

500
00:22:25.977 --> 00:22:28.104
All right. see you soon.

501
00:22:30.315 --> 00:22:32.817
- [dogs barking]
- [Dexter] <i>Great. Police dogs.</i>

502
00:22:32.859 --> 00:22:35.028
<i>I hope they have as much fun
running around the woods</i>

503
00:22:35.070 --> 00:22:37.072
<i>as I did last night.</i>

504
00:22:42.202 --> 00:22:44.329
Thanks for making it out
on short notice.

505
00:22:44.371 --> 00:22:46.373
It's how it always is.

506
00:22:46.414 --> 00:22:48.667
Nobody ever plans on
going missing.

507
00:22:48.708 --> 00:22:51.211
- Hey. little guy...
- [Rusty] Yo! Yo. yo. yo.

508
00:22:51.253 --> 00:22:53.213
No touching.

509
00:22:53.255 --> 00:22:54.548
They don't need no confusion

510
00:22:54.589 --> 00:22:56.841
- with your petting.
